        "parts": [
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "وَمُرْ أَهْلَ مَكَّةَ أَلَّا يَأْخُذُوا مِنْ سَاكِنٍ أَجْراً، فَإِنَّ اللهَ سُبْحَانَهُ يَقُولُ"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:2:67:4",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/2/67/404",
      "text": [
        " ﴿سَوَاءً الْعَاكِفُ فِيهِ وَالْبَادِ﴾"
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
          "Ask the people of Mecca not to charge rent from lodgers, because Allāh, the Glorified, says that: “alike; for the dweller therein as well as the stranger” (Qur’ān, 22:25)."
        ]
      }
    },
